Instructions on how to assign process id in CDRS:

Step 1: Click on Edit button.

Step 2: Click on the Lookup button of Assigned Process Id field.

Step 3: In the Lookup window, search for the PID and select it by clicking on the hyperlink.

Step 4: Ensure the selected PID appears on the Assigned Process Id field.

Step 5: Click on Update button to save changes.


Additional note: CDRS Status after Process Id is assigned

1. CDRS is 'Closed' when Assigned Pid Lifecycle (PLM) is 'MPW Ready', 'Prototype Ready' and 'Available'.

2. CDRS status is 'Registered/TBO PID Assigned' when Assigned Pid Lifecycle (PLM) is 'Registered/TBO' . To close this CDRS, process owner is required to promote PID lifecycle in PLM from 'Registered/TBOâ€™ to either 'MPW Ready', 'Prototype Ready' or 'Available'.

